Some are very close to the Muslim Brotherhood.
Unsurprisingly, it is most often unanimously that the articles have been voted on.
Some commentators were amused by the fact that one of the day's differences had been expressed around... the hour of prayer, some members of the committee felt that the constituent's pendulum was ill-regulated.
The text, which was still being voted last night, contains 234 articles.
Subjects of all attention, article 2 is finally identical to that of the 1971 Constitution, stating that "the principles of sharia are the main source of law."
Salafist parties, for whom Islamic law is a major claim, hoped they could replace "the principles" with "the rules", which would have allowed for stricter application.
