In the current state of affairs, the disappearance of these systems can be considered to benefit liberal-type democracies as a kind of pause before a new stage.
The fact that the current elites completely ignore the possibility of hundreds of thousands of future human losses, the humanitarian and social crises that we are now witnesses and the crimes against humanity as we know them from the past and recent history.
The repeal of the Public Use Act is not a solution, at least in the long term.
